'''The Adasca BioMechanical Corporation of Arkania''',<ref name="KOTOR 17 Financial Report">{{KOTORbackups|17}}</ref> known simply as '''Adascorp''', was a vast medical corporation from [[Arkania/Legends|Arkania]]. Famous for its [[Bioengineering/Legends|bioengineering]] and medical research advances, Adascorp was allied with the [[Draay Trust]] and [[Czerka Arms/Legends|Czerka Corporation]]. It was owned by the [[House of Adasca]] and brought huge amounts of profit to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]], forming [[Adascopolis]].

For [[Standard year/Legends|years]], Adascorp headquarters was located on the massive [[Starship/Legends|starship]] ''[[Arkanian Legacy]]''. However, the ship was lost along with [[Lord/Legends|Lord]] [[Arkoh Adasca]] in his ill-fated [[First Battle of Omonoth|attempt]] to secure [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] power through [[Project Black Harvest|Operation Dark Harvest]]. The loss of the ship and its extensive archives and research facilities set Adascorp research back by [[Standard decade/Legends|decades]]. Worse, with no explicit heir to Arkoh's controlling interest in the corporation, ownership of the company remained contested. Adasca's niece [[Aurora Adasca|Aurora]] was the sole heir of the company, but in her absence the [[Draay Trust]] filed to take over Adascorp.

During the [[Cold War (Galactic Republic–Sith Empire)|Cold War]], Adascorp worked with the [[Republic Strategic Information Service]] and [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Jun Seros (Jedi)|Jun Seros]] in preparing a trap for the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Grand Champion of the Great Hunt]]. They did this by offering a legitimate deal where they offered [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] in exchange for the hunter for sponsoring their new line of [[adrenal]]s on [[Quesh]]. The bounty hunter arrived at the scene where they met the [[Director of Public Relations]] who was actually an SIS [[Agent/Legends|agent]] in disguise. Afterwards, [[Mako (slicer)|Mako]] commented that the offer was legitimate and the Grand Champion commented that Adascorp was working with the Republic to bring them into custody. The bounty hunter later received an email from the Adascorp Director of Galactic Relations apologizing for "an incident that occurred during your recent visit to our Quesh refinement facility" and offering some credits as a "complimentary gift to make up for your visit being cut short."

